# Turn state tracking: session_state turn=agent before LLM, mark_response_sent after channel send

## Requirements

- TODO: Add requirements

## Acceptance Criteria

- TODO: Add acceptance criteria

## Implementation

- Files: `src/session.ml`, channel handlers (telegram.ml, discord.ml, slack.ml, slack_socket.ml)
- Add helper functions (inline in session.ml or new session_persistence.ml):
  - `upsert_session_state ~db ~session_key ~turn ?channel ?channel_id ()`
  - `mark_response_sent ~db ~session_key ()`
  - `load_pending_agent_sessions ~db ~max_age_seconds` → `(string * string option * string option) list`
- In session.ml `turn` and `turn_stream`: call upsert_session_state with turn="agent" BEFORE Agent.turn call; pass channel/channel_id via new optional params
- In each channel handler: call mark_response_sent AFTER successful channel send
- Thread channel_id through session.ml:turn as optional parameter

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] session_state row created/updated with turn="agent" before every LLM call
- [ ] session_state.response_sent_at set and turn="user" after successful channel send
- [ ] load_pending_agent_sessions returns sessions with turn="agent" AND response_sent_at IS NULL AND last_active > cutoff
- [ ] channel and channel_id stored correctly for Telegram, Discord, Slack sessions
